For this project, we utilized a comprehensive dataset of tomato plant leaf images, essential for training and evaluating our disease detection model.

ðŸ“‚ Download the Dataset: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/kaustubhb999/tomatoleaf

The dataset can be downloaded from Kaggle using the following link: Tomato Leaf Disease Dataset.

ðŸ“¦ What's Inside:

-Training and Test Images: High-resolution images of tomato leaves are categorized into different classes, representing healthy leaves and those affected by various diseases.
- Annotations: Labels indicating the disease type or whether the leaf is healthy are crucial for supervised learning.
- Variety: The dataset includes images captured under different conditions and from various angles, ensuring a diverse and robust training set for model generalization.

This dataset forms the backbone of our machine learning model, enabling it to accurately identify and classify tomato leaf diseases.
